definitions.definition: The first existence of anything; act or fact of commencing; the beginning .
examples: The time of Henry VII nearly coincides with the commencement of what is termed modern history.

definitions.definition: The day when degrees are conferred by colleges and universities upon students and others.
A graduation ceremony , from a school, college or university. Sometimes before the actual graduation.
